-- New World Resources Rises From July Low as Coal Price Increases
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-07-16T12:49:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-16/new-world-resources-rises-from-july-low-as-coal-price-increases.html
New World Resources Plc (NWR) , a Czech
coal-mining company, rebounded from last week’s drop to the
lowest this month as the price of the commodity increased.  The stock climbed 1.8 percent to 102.80 koruna by 2:33 p.m.
in  Prague , after falling 3.9 percent in the previous five days
to the lowest since June 28. Europe’s benchmark coal derivatives
added 0.2 percent to $96.50 a metric ton in the Netherlands.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  